## 🚀 How to Run — Step by Step

### Prerequisites

> [!IMPORTANT]
> You need these installed before starting:
> - **Java 21** (JDK)
> - **Maven** (or use the included [mvnw](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/OneDrive/Documents/Projects/Spring_AI%20Project/mvnw) wrapper)
> - **Docker** (for PostgreSQL + PGVector)
> - **Ollama** (for local AI models)

---

### Step 1: Install & Start Ollama

Download Ollama from [ollama.com](https://ollama.com) and install it.

Then pull the required models:

```bash
# Pull the chat model (Gemma 3, 1B parameter version)
ollama pull gemma3:1b

# Pull the embedding model
ollama pull nomic-embed-text:latest
```

Verify Ollama is running:
```bash
ollama list
```

You should see both `gemma3:1b` and `nomic-embed-text:latest` listed.

> [!NOTE]
> Ollama runs on `http://localhost:11434` by default. The app is already configured to connect there.

---

### Step 2: Start PostgreSQL with PGVector (Docker)

From the project root directory:

```bash
docker-compose up -d
```

This starts a PostgreSQL 18 instance with PGVector extension on **port 5433**.

Verify it's running:
```bash
docker ps
```

You should see a container named `ChatBot-local`.

> [!TIP]
> Database credentials (already configured in [application.yaml](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/OneDrive/Documents/Projects/Spring_AI%20Project/src/main/resources/application.yaml)):
> - **URL**: `jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5433/ChatBot-db`
> - **User**: `user`
> - **Password**: `chatbot`

---

### Step 3: Build & Run the Spring Boot Backend

```bash
# Using Maven wrapper (recommended)
./mvnw spring-boot:run

# OR using system Maven
mvn spring-boot:run
```

Wait until you see:
```
Started ChatBotApplication in X.XX seconds
```

The backend API will be available at **http://localhost:8080**

> [!WARNING]
> Make sure Ollama and PostgreSQL are running BEFORE starting the backend, otherwise the app will fail to connect.

---

### Step 4: Open the Frontend

Simply open the frontend in your browser:

```bash
# Option A: Double-click the file
# Open: frontend/index.html in your browser

# Option B: Use a local server (recommended for best experience)
cd frontend
python -m http.server 5500
# Then open http://localhost:5500
```

> [!TIP]
> Using a local HTTP server avoids potential CORS issues with `file://` protocol.

---

### Step 5: Upload a PDF & Start Chatting!

1. **Scroll down** to the **Upload** section
2. **Drag & drop** a PDF file (or click to browse)
3. Wait for the upload and embedding process to complete ✅
4. **Scroll down** to the **Chat** section
5. **Select your document** from the sidebar
6. **Type a question** and press Enter!

---

## 🔌 API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Parameters | Description |
|--------|----------|-----------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/documents/upload` | `file` (multipart) | Upload a PDF for processing |
| `GET` | `/documents/chat` | `query`, `docName` | Ask a question about a document |

### Example API Calls

```bash
# Upload a PDF
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/documents/upload \
  -F "file=@my-document.pdf"

# Chat with the uploaded document
curl "http://localhost:8080/documents/chat?query=What%20is%20the%20main%20topic&docName=my-document.pdf"
```

---

## 🧩 Key Backend Components

### [DocChatController.java](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/OneDrive/Documents/Projects/Spring_AI%20Project/src/main/java/com/example/ChatBot/DocChatController.java)
- **Upload endpoint**: Receives PDF, delegates to [IngestionService](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/OneDrive/Documents/Projects/Spring_AI%20Project/src/main/java/com/example/ChatBot/IngestionService.java#18-48)
- **Chat endpoint**: Uses `QuestionAnswerAdvisor` with vector store similarity search (top-4 chunks, 0.7 threshold), filtered by document name

### [IngestionService.java](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/OneDrive/Documents/Projects/Spring_AI%20Project/src/main/java/com/example/ChatBot/IngestionService.java)
- Reads PDF page-by-page using `PagePdfDocumentReader`
- Splits text into 800-token chunks via `TokenTextSplitter`
- Adds `source` metadata (filename) to each chunk
- Stores embeddings in PGVector

### [WebConfig.java](file:///c:/Users/LENOVO/OneDrive/Documents/Projects/Spring_AI%20Project/src/main/java/com/example/ChatBot/Config/WebConfig.java) *(NEW)*
- Enables CORS for all origins so the frontend can call the backend API

---

## 🎨 Frontend Features

- ✨ **Premium dark-mode** design with glassmorphism and gradient accents
- 🎯 **Drag & drop** PDF upload with animated progress bar
- 💬 **Real-time chat** interface with typing indicators
- 📱 **Fully responsive** — works on mobile, tablet, and desktop
- 🎭 **Scroll animations** — elements animate in on scroll
- 🔖 **Document selector** sidebar shows model info and search parameters
- 💡 **Example queries** — quick-start buttons for common questions

